properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 10 at 4:03AM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
...Periods of Wintry Precipitation, Possibly Significant, Tonight
Through Saturday Night...

* WHAT...A mix of freezing rain and sleet is possible very late
tonight, mainly across the northern part of the county, with
chances for a light to moderate mix spreading across the rest of
the county into later Saturday morning and afternoon. The mixed
precipitation will change over to a period of snow, possibly
briefly heavy, Saturday evening. Total ice accumulations in
excess of one tenth of an inch are possible late tonight into
Saturday, mainly over northern Cook. Total snow accumulations in
excess of 3 inches are also possible Saturday evening, with the
highest amounts over northern Cook. Northeast winds will gust
40 to 50 mph along the lake front and 40 to 45 mph further
inland overnight and Saturday.

* WHERE...Northern Cook County.

* WHEN...Late tonight through Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
